events.name: GDG Chapel Hill Meet and Greet
events.description: This is our first official event where we plan on introducing the members to plans for GDG Chapel Hill for 2020 as well as have the members to meet each other and network. We will have a brief presentation done by the core team about themselves and further discuss the roadmap for GDG Chapel Hill. This will be more of a brainstorming session as we'll be taking suggestions from all the members about the plans for future events.
events.how_to_find_us: The event is held at the Main Event Space inside 1789 Venture Lab.

upcoming.name: Firebase Study Jam
upcoming.description:
Want to get started building web apps? Learn how to do that with Firebase!

Join a community of like-minded developers and explore the latest Firebase for Web technologies as a team. Together we'll work through Firebase for web codelabs prepared by Google instructors. By the end of the workshop, you'll be able to build your web apps like a pro!

Bring a laptop and charger (PC, Mac, or Chromebook)! The labs will run on all of the latest versions of popular browsers.
For the best experience check out: https://firebase.google.com/docs/web/setup
(Don't forget your charger !)

Agenda

6:00 pm: Introduction to Firebase

7:30 pm: Break

8:00 pm: Codelab- Build a web app from scratch

9:00 pm: Event ends

organizers.name: Aditya B.
organizers.bio: I am a maker, innovator and tech-enthusiast. I love working with new and interesting people in the developer & maker community. I've been a part of the developer ecosystem in India and US since last 3 years now. Also I'm an Undergrad at UNC CH.
